1. MGX invested $2 billion in Binance, setting a new record in the crypto industry;
2. Amber DWM merged with iClick and will start trading on Nasdaq using the AMBR stock code;
3. The US SEC's lawsuit against Ripple may end soon and has entered the final stage;
4. Video sharing platform Rumble purchased 188 BTC for $17.1 million;
5. CBOE submitted a Solana ETF application for Franklin;
6. The co-founder of Russia's sanctioned crypto trading platform Garantex was arrested in India;
7. Massachusetts legislators proposed the establishment of a special committee on blockchain and cryptocurrency;
8. Nebraska signed a Bitcoin ATM regulatory bill;
9. Arkham: ARK Invest Fund stopped selling Bitcoin and bought more than $10 million in Coinbase shares this week;
10. GnosisDAO invested another $4.8 million to support HOPR in developing a decentralized VPN;
11. Japanese tech giant Sony partners with LINE to advance Web3.
